1. The Only Limit To Our Realization Of Tomorrow Will Be Our Doubts Of Today.
2. What You Lack In Talent Can Be Made Up With Desire, Hustle And Giving 110% All The Time.
3. Do What You Can With All You Have, Wherever You Are.
4. Develop An ‘Attitude Of Gratitude’. Say Thank You To Everyone You Meet For Everything They Do For You.
5. You Are Never Too Old To Set Another Goal Or To Dream A New Dream.
6. To See What Is Right And Not Do It Is A Lack Of Courage.
7. Reading Is To The Mind, As Exercise Is To The Body.
8. Fake It Until You Make It! Act As If You Had All The Confidence You Require Until It Becomes Your Reality.
9. The Future Belongs To The Competent. Get Good, Get Better, Be The Best!
10. For Every Reason It’s Not Possible, There Are Hundreds Of People Who Have Faced The Same Circumstances And Succeeded.
11. Things Work Out Best For Those Who Make The Best Of How Things Work Out.
12. A Room Without Books Is Like A Body Without A Soul.
13. I Think Goals Should Never Be Easy, They Should Force You To Work, Even If They Are Uncomfortable At The Time.
14. One Of The Lessons That I Grew Up With Was To Always Stay True To Yourself And Never Let What Somebody Else Says Distract You From Your Goals.
15. Today’s Accomplishments Were Yesterday’s Impossibilities.”
